    "title": "Constant-size timed metadata sample data"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Some clients using timed metadata tracks may prefer to create metadata tracks with samples that have the same size. Two approaches are described here.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In one approach, the metadata written might contain a fixed number of fixed-sized metadata values (for example, integers or statically sized structures). If one or more values are not used, atoms corresponding to unused values can have their ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "local_key_id",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " value set to an unreferenced value (such as ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ").",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the second approach, the size of individual metadata values may vary. It is possible to create constant-sized metadata samples by determining a maximum timed metadata media sample size and using unreferenced atoms to add up to this size. The approach is:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Determine the constant metadata media atom size desired.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Fill in the atoms holding metadata values (see the Timed metadata media sample structure example in ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.qtff/documentation/QuickTime-File-Format/Timed_metadata_sample_data_format",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "type": "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ").",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "If necessary, add one or more unreferenced atoms to reach the constant metadata media atom size.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Because an atom has a minimum size of 8 bytes, the sum of the sizes of contained timed metadata media samples either must equal the target constant metadata media atom size, or must be 8 or more bytes smaller than the target constant atom size to allow for one or more padding atoms.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Unreferenced-or-NULL-timed-metadata-sample-data",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Unreferenced or NULL timed metadata sample data",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A timed metadata sample is identified by its derived atom type supplied by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "local_key_id",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " value in the metadata sample description’s key tables. An unreferenced metadata atom, meaning one which is not identified in the key tables and not having the reserved value ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0xFFFFFFFF",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", can be considered a “NULL” metadata media sample since its type is unknown in the local namespace and its data will not be interpreted. There is no prescribed atom type indicating a NULL metadata sample although a type of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is recommended, as mentioned in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.qtff/documentation/quicktime-file-format/Metadata_key_atom",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " description. Using unreferenced atoms presents a useful way to supply padding when structuring a track for constant-sized metadata sample data or when there are runs of no-metadata interspersed with runs of metadata in a given track, instead of using multiple track edits.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
